The Chronicle Mthabisi Tshuma, Showbiz Correspondent
The Confederation of Zimbabwe Retailers (CZR), the biggest retail business representative in the country has approached Government to consider the reopening of bars and nightclubs which have become white elephants since they were closed on March 23. CZR president Mr Denford Mutashu said the retailers have been greatly affected by the closure of these outlets as they have lost out on business. They said they are keeping their fingers crossed as alcoholic beverages retail and wholesale players have readied themselves to comply with Covid-19 requirements in reopening. Phathisani Nkomo who owns nightspots Cosmopolitan, Havana, Cubana and Zarah Lounge said they are working flat out to ensure they reopen.  â€¦more to follow